=====Usage notes=====
This is one of only four everyday kanji with a five-[[mora]] reading, and one of only two nouns. The only other common kanji with five-mora readings are {{lang|ja|承}} in the verb {{ja-r|承る|うけたまわる}}, {{lang|ja|慮}} in the verb {{ja-r|慮る|おもんぱかる}}, and {{ja-r|志|こころざし}}. No kanji in common use has a six- or more mora reading. See also {{ja-r|謀|はかりごと}}.

The unusually long reading is due to it representing a triple compound word, analyzed as {{ja-r|御%言%宣|み%こと%のり}}, yielding 1 + 2 + 2 = 5.

